figgy.title: An ephemera folder is an image resource

comments.body: @hackartisan This looks good. I'm not sure about other use cases. Does this feel safe to merge?

I dug into this a bit more and that flag is only used for make decisions about which characterization service to run. It was added in https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/pull/1394/files in a way that looks to me like it's about distinguishing images resources from geo resources. The only thing that holds me back is I don't really know why we *wouldn't* want to run imagemagick on anything with the right mime type https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/93764af4ee1b70fe06cff7e6c9da73157e499049/config/config.yml#L222-L224 So I don't really have a grasp of why that flag is there to begin with.

I'm about 90% comfortable just merging it but it might be nice to see if @tpendragon would weigh in and it does seem like we have enough space on the timeline for that.

orangelight.title: Don't Display Labels of Empty values in the holdings display section

comments.body: This issue seems to be specific to our checks within the holdings display section.  When I create solr documents with empty fields and load them in as fixtures, Blacklight is smart enough not to display the fields.  However, when it comes to arrays within the holdings_1display JSON, it looks like our custom check was not checking whether or not they were empty.
